                    in an external file.
                </h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Event binders get burried in source code.</li>
                    <li>Difficult for code maintainers to know where code is happening.</li>
                    <li>Executes event binders and functions not needed for every page.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h2>Adapt a JavaScript Pattern</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Creates more reusable code</li>
                    <li>More scalable</li>
                    <li>Can be expensive</li>

                    <li>Additional Reading:<a href="http://addyosmani.com/resources/essentialjsdesignpatterns/book/" target="_blank">Learning JavaScript Design Patterns by Addy Osmani</a></li>
                </ul>
                <!--                    <img src="Gifs/YqdNz.gif" class="fragment" />-->
            </section>
            <section>
                <h3>Example Basic Pattern</h3>
                <pre><code class="javascript short-code">//Pass in jQuery so I can use $ wherever I want without conflict
//Pass in document and alias it to d for shorter code.
var HomeIndex = (function ($, d) {
    
    //Private variables & functions
    var _init;
    _init = function () { };
    return {
        //Public Events
        Init: _init
    };
})(jQuery, document);</code></pre>
                <pre><code>&lt;script&gt;
    $(function () {
        HomeIndex.Init();
    });
&lt;/script&gt;
                        </code></pre>
